        Called when the device has been connected. This does not mean that the application may start communication. A service discovery will be handled automatically after this call. Service discovery may ends up with calling BleManagerCallbacks.onServicesDiscovered(boolean) or BleManagerCallbacks.onDeviceNotSupported() if required services have not been found.

        Specified by:

      • onServicesDiscovered

        public void onServicesDiscovered(boolean optionalServicesFound)
        Description copied from interface: BleManagerCallbacks
        Called when service discovery has finished and primary services has been found. The device is ready to operate. This method is not called if the primary, mandatory services were not found during service discovery. For example in the Blood Pressure Monitor, a Blood Pressure service is a primary service and Intermediate Cuff Pressure service is a optional secondary service. Existence of battery service is not notified by this call.
        Specified by:
        onServicesDiscovered in interface BleManagerCallbacks
        Parameters:
        optionalServicesFound - if true the secondary services were also found on the device.
